  "prompt": "Is Tufts University a good college (moreover, a good engineering college)?",
  "response": "Tufts University is generally considered a good college and has a solid reputation, particularly for its emphasis on interdisciplinary studies and its programs in the liberal arts and sciences. The university is located in Medford, Massachusetts, just outside of Boston, which provides students with access to a vibrant urban environment and numerous opportunities for internships and research.\n\nIn terms of engineering, Tufts has a well-regarded School of Engineering that offers a range of undergraduate and graduate programs. It is known for its strengths in biomedical engineering, computer science, and mechanical engineering, among others. The school emphasizes a collaborative and hands-on approach to engineering education, integrating technical training with liberal arts to produce well-rounded graduates.\n\nOverall, whether Tufts is a good fit for you may depend on your specific interests, goals, and values regarding education. It\u2019s always a good idea to visit the campus, talk to current students or alumni, and explore specific programs to see if they align with your aspirations.",
